label.value: BAC Regimen

label.value: R-ACVBP Regimen

label.value: Choroidal and Ciliary Body Melanoma by AJCC v8 Stage

label.value: Stage I Choroidal and Ciliary Body Melanoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage I includes: T1a, N0, M0. T1a: Tumor size category 1 without ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage II Choroidal and Ciliary Body Melanoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage II includes: IIA (T1b-d, N0, M0); (T2a, N0, M0); IIB (T2b, N0, M0); (T3a, N0, M0).  T1b: Tumor size category 1 with ciliary body involvement.  T1c: Tumor size category 1 without ciliary body involvement but with extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter.  T1d: Tumor size category 1 with ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter. T2a: Tumor size category 2 without ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension. T2b: Tumor size category 2 with ciliary body involvement. T3a: Tumor size category 3 without ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIA Choroidal and Ciliary Body Melanoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIA includes: (T1b-d, N0, M0); (T2a, N0, M0).  T1b: Tumor size category 1 with ciliary body involvement.  T1c: Tumor size category 1 without ciliary body involvement but with extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter.  T1d: Tumor size category 1 with ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter. T2a: Tumor size category 2 without ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIB Choroidal and Ciliary Body Melanoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIB includes: (T2b, N0, M0); (T3a, N0, M0).  T2b: Tumor size category 2 with ciliary body involvement. T3a: Tumor size category 3 without ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage III Choroidal and Ciliary Body Melanoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage III includes: IIIA (T2c-d, N0, M0); (T3b-c, N0, M0); (T4a, N0, M0); IIIB (T3d, N0, M0); (T4b-c, N0, M0); IIIC: (T4d-e, N0, M0). T2c: Tumor size category 2 without ciliary body involvement but with extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter. T2d: Tumor size category 2 with ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter. T3b: Tumor size category 3 with ciliary body involvement. T3c: Tumor size category 3 without ciliary body involvement but with extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter. T4a: Tumor size category 4 without ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension. T3d: Tumor size category 3 with ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter.  T4b: Tumor size category 4 with ciliary body involvement. T4c: Tumor size category 4 without ciliary body involvement but with extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter. T4d: Tumor size category 4 with ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter. T4e: Any tumor size category with extraocular extension more than 5 mm in largest diameter. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIA Choroidal and Ciliary Body Melanoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIIA includes: (T2c-d, N0, M0); (T3b-c, N0, M0); (T4a, N0, M0). T2c: Tumor size category 2 without ciliary body involvement but with extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter. T2d: Tumor size category 2 with ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter. T3b: Tumor size category 3 with ciliary body involvement. T3c: Tumor size category 3 without ciliary body involvement but with extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter. T4a: Tumor size category 4 without ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIB Choroidal and Ciliary Body Melanoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIIB includes: (T3d, N0, M0); (T4b-c, N0, M0). T3d: Tumor size category 3 with ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter.  T4b: Tumor size category 4 with ciliary body involvement. T4c: Tumor size category 4 without ciliary body involvement but with extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIC Choroidal and Ciliary Body Melanoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIIC includes: T4d-e, N0, M0. T4d: Tumor size category 4 with ciliary body involvement and extraocular extension less than or equal to 5 mm in largest diameter. T4e: Any tumor size category with extraocular extension more than 5 mm in largest diameter. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Choroidal and Ciliary Body Melanoma AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IV includes: (Any T, N1, M0); (Any T, Any N, M1a-c). N1: Regional lymph node metastasis or discrete tumor deposits in the orbit. M0: No distant metastasis. M1a: Distant metastasis, with the largest diameter of the largest metastasis measuring 3 cm or less. M1b: Distant metastasis, with the largest diameter of the largest metastasis measuring 3.1-8.0 cm. M1c: Distant metastasis, with the largest diameter of the largest metastasis measuring 8.1 cm or more.  (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Minor Response in Neuroblastoma

value.value: Partial response or complete response in at least one component (i.e., soft tissue, bone, and bone marrow disease) but at least one other component with stable disease; no component with progressive disease. (J Clin Oncol 35: 2580-2587, 2017)
A chromosome band present on 14q

label.value: Total Measured Tumor Burden

value.value: The sum of the longest diameters of non-nodal target and new measurable lesions, and the short axes of nodal target and new measurable lesions.

label.value: Progressive Disease in Neuroblastoma

value.value: Any component (i.e., soft tissue, bone, and bone marrow disease) with progressive disease. (J Clin Oncol 35: 2580-2587, 2017)

label.value: Uveal Melanoma by AJCC v7 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of uveal melanoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: R-CHOPE Regimen

value.value: A regimen consisting of rituximab, cyclophosphamide, doxorubicin, vincristine, prednisone and etoposide that can be used in the treatment of non-Hodgkin lymphomas (NHL). R-CHOPE differs from R-EPOCH in the drug doses and schedule of the administration of the various drugs.

label.value: Carboplatin/Pembrolizumab/Pemetrexed Regimen

value.value: A regimen consisting of carboplatin, pembrolizumab and pemetrexed that can be used in the treatment of non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC).

label.value: Retinoblastoma TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of retinoblastoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system. This classification does not apply to central nervous system component of "trilateral retinoblastoma" (is staged according to the classification for brain and spinal cord), retinoma (or retinocytoma) (no AJCC staging system), and medulloepithelioma (no AJCC staging system). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Retinoblastoma Clinical TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of retinoblastoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Retinoblastoma Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of retinoblastoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Retinoblastoma cM0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Retinoblastoma with no signs or symptoms of intracranial or distant metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Retinoblastoma cM1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Retinoblastoma with distant metastasis without microscopic confirmation. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Acidic Region

value.value: Any portion of a protein molecule with a net negative charge.

label.value: Retinoblastoma cM1a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Retinoblastoma with tumor(s) involving any distant site (e.g., bone marrow, liver) on clinical or radiologic tests. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Retinoblastoma cM1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Retinoblastoma with tumor involving the CNS on radiologic imaging (not including trilateral retinoblastoma). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Retinoblastoma Clinical Primary Tumor TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of retinoblastoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. Each eye is scored for cT criteria, and the cT category for the patient is based on the most advanced eye. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Retinoblastoma cTX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Unknown evidence of intraocular tumor. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
